context: The word 'teisi' is the partitive plural form of 'teine' (other/different) in Estonian. It is commonly used to mean 'other notes' or 'different notes'. The dictionary definition shows it's related to taking on different notes or changing one's approach/style. In music context, specifically means playing other notes instead of the current ones. Can also imply changing direction or method.
